				\begin{document}$${{{\mathrm{M}}}} = \frac{{I_{ph} - I_d}}{{I_{bg}}}$$\end{document}, where Iph represents the photocurrent, Id is the dark current and Ibg denotes the net-photocurrent when M = 1. It is determined as 1.2 × 103 @ −20 V (Supplementary Fig. S5), no less than that of bulk counterpart37.
